cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with processing RGB-D data to build 3D point clouds and labeling objects in them. This is a core computer vision task and hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper also mentions the successful application of the proposed algorithms on a mobile robot for finding objects in a cluttered room. This indicates that the paper is relevant to the field of robotics and hence cs.RO is the second most likely sub-category. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a graphical model that captures various features and contextual relations for object labeling. This is a machine learning approach and hence cs.AI is a likely sub-category. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a maximum-margin learning approach to train the proposed graphical model. This indicates that the paper is relevant to the field of machine learning and hence cs.LG is a likely sub-category. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with building 3D point clouds of indoor scenes. This involves some aspects of computer graphics and hence cs.GR is a possible sub-category.
